 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Gojirax</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Just my $0.02 worth.</P><P>- I've had two characters first names changed. (Didn't pay for either and one was level 51 at the time.) One was done within a day, the other took two months because our server GM was only on during certain times and my luck in getting past the Guides was based on whether they thought my reasons merited GM involvement. In the end I got what I wanted and didn't suffer a bit for it.</P><P>- I've had half a dozen corpses summoned from messed up places (And a few live bodies summoned from being stuck in walls etc.) usually within 10 minutes of petitioning my dilemma.</P><P>- I've had two Customer Service 100% rezzes when a wipeout or death was caused by the game and nothing I did.</P><P>- I've had gripes or disputes settled fairly (Not always in my favor, but fairly.) every time I've had to petition. (Maybe a half dozen times in 3 years.)</P><P>- I've had GM's reset/fix bugged mobs (Like Vox, Inny) always within 10-15 minutes of a petition.</P><P>- I've never had a petition go ignored.</P><P>Perhaps it's bad luck in general that some folks have, perhaps it's the wording of their petitions. (I know how frustrating things can get and sometimes taking a deep breath before composing a petition is a good idea.) Perhaps it's the customer service frustration levels on various servers, but I've had nothing but top notch customer service in my 3 years in Everquest and can't fault them for much at all personally. (Especially since these are mostly Volunteers I'm pretty sure.)</P><P>You have my sympathy for your troubles though.</P><P>Regards,<BR>Goji</P><P><BR><img src="http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojirax.jpg" border=0></font></td>
